{
  "texts": [
    "The dissociation protocol that was previously used on brain tissue 50, was optimized here to maximize the nuclei isolation for the liver tissue.",
    "The protocol after the optimization included the following steps: first, thawing tissue sample was cut into smaller pieces, minced and transferred into a glass dounce homogenizer.",
    "30 strokes of pestle A were used to homogenize the tissue in 0.3 M Sucrose (Sigma) solution including 0.002 M EDTA (Thermo Scientific), 1% BSA (Serva), and 1% Tergitol solution (Sigma).",
    "After 5 min of incubation, next 30 strokes of pestle B were applied to finalize the disruption process and deliberate nuclei from the cells into suspension.",
    "Homogenized solution was centrifuged at 600 g for 5 min and the nuclei pellet was washed twice in PBS solution (0.002 M EDTA, 1% BSA, 0.2 U/ul RNase Inhibitor (Thermo Scientific))."
  ]
}